<TITLE> Body of another BDR man found in Peelkhana </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com)Police recovered on Friday the dead body of a border guard from the BDR headquarters at Peelkhana in the city, raising the deaths to 30 from reported suicides, heart attacks and other diseases since the Feb 25-26 mutiny. Rafiqul Islam, 27, badge no-67225, was employed as signals man in Rifles Battalion-33. Shahnewaz, sub-inspector of New Market Police Station, told bdnews24.com that police retrieved the dangling body from a bathroom at the eastern side of floor-5 of ISB Line at around 2pm. Islam's neck was tied with a handkerchief to a window grille. The body was later sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for autopsy and an unnatural death cases was filed at around 3pm. bdnews24.com DMCH correspondent said police took the body to Dhaka Medical College Hospital at around 10pm. According to the inquest, done in presence of a magistrate, the face was covered with a handkerchief and his legs touched the floor. bdne
